    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-14T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="282"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/125a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-14T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1564. For <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">John F. Stevens</persName> [from <persName
                        corresp="#p_WD1">Daniel Willard</persName>]:</p>
                <p>Endeavoring secure money from Treasury to enable compliance your several cables
                    regarding purchase locomotives, cars and machinery for erection Vladivostok.
                    Cable full description shop <pb facs="0244" n="194" xml:id="pg_194"/> buildings
                    agreed upon, also if traveling cranes intended, give distance between centers of
                    rails on runways, also height from runway to floor and height to underside of
                    roof truss, and exact type Brown cranes suggested. Also advise what use boilers
                    will be put to and number required. Important complete information sufficient
                    make intelligent purchase here. Five hundred locomotives and 10,000 cars already
                    ordered. Fifteen hundred locomotives, 30,000 cars under consideration. Consider
                    it unnecessary erect shops Vladivostok if money can not be provided for
                    remainder locomotive and car requirements.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
